/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.log
/.qmlls.ini
**/.qmlls.ini

# rustfmt backups
**/*.orig

# Build artifacts that may sneak in
*.pdb
*.exe
*.dSYM/

# Compiled Qt translation catalogs. The .ts sources are tracked; the .qm
# binaries are produced by `just l10n-release` and installed at package time.
/apps/linsync-gui/i18n/*.qm

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
.zed/

# AI coding-agent instruction files, kept local-only (not source-tracked).
# CLAUDE.md is a symlink to AGENTS.md; GEMINI.md is optional / per-developer.
/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md
/GEMINI.md

# Long-form project roadmap, kept local-only (not source-tracked).
/PLAN.md

# Local secrets / credentials. Should never be committed. If you need
# to share configuration with collaborators, put it under packaging/
# or docs/ and review it explicitly.
.env
.env.*
*.env
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*_rsa
**/*_dsa
**/id_*
**/credentials
**/credentials.*
**/secrets.*
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx

# Editor swap / temp / backup files
**/*.tmp.*
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~

# Cargo / flatpak vendor scratch. The dev `.cargo/config.toml`
# (mold+sccache wiring) IS checked in — only transient cargo
# scratch like a flatpak-build-time vendor swap or a `.bak`
# restore file are ignored. `/vendor/` guards against an
# accidental top-level `cargo vendor` (the supported path puts
# the tree at target/flatpak/vendor).
/.cargo/*
!/.cargo/config.toml
/vendor/

# flatpak-builder writes its build cache + git mirror to this hidden
# dir at the workspace root, separate from /target/.
/.flatpak-builder/

# Distro artifacts at the workspace root. `just flatpak-bundle` and
# the per-distro recipes write into target/release*/ ; these patterns
# catch artifacts that land at the root (e.g. linuxdeploy renames
# LinSync-*.AppImage in-place before the script moves it).
/*.AppImage
/*.flatpak
/*.deb
/*.rpm
/*.pkg.tar.zst
/packaging/arch/*.pkg.tar.zst
/packaging/arch/pkg/
/packaging/arch/src/

# Archive fixture source tree and built archives — regenerated at test time by
# tests/fixtures/archive/build.sh. Allowlist the committed files; everything
# else is ignored so test scratch outputs don't leak in.
/tests/fixtures/archive/*
!/tests/fixtures/archive/build.sh
!/tests/fixtures/archive/members.txt

# Symlink and permissions fixture trees — regenerated at test time by their
# respective build.sh scripts; only the scripts themselves are checked in.
/tests/fixtures/symlink/left/
/tests/fixtures/symlink/right/
/tests/fixtures/permissions/left/
/tests/fixtures/permissions/right/

# Local release-validation staging dirs. `dist/` is the canonical name
# scripts/release-vm-validation.sh defaults to; `dist-rc1/` (and any
# `dist-*` variant) holds the artifacts pulled from the GitHub Release
# during pre-tag validation. None of these are source-tracked.
/dist/
/dist-*/

# Local containerised RPM build output from `just package-rpm-fedora44`.
# The build script also lives in packaging/rpm/, but its rpmbuild tree
# (_rpmbuild-fedora44/) is local-only scratch.
/packaging/rpm/_rpmbuild-fedora44/
/packaging/rpm/_rpmbuild/
# `just package-rpm` regenerates the source tarball each build via
# `git archive` (linsync-<version>.tar.gz). The spec + build scripts in
# packaging/rpm/ are tracked; the archived tree is transient.
/packaging/rpm/*.tar.gz

# Debian `dpkg-buildpackage` scratch. The packaging sources live in
# packaging/debian/ (tracked) and get copied/symlinked to a `debian/`
# root for the build; debian/rules then points CARGO_HOME and the
# staging tree there, and debhelper adds its own stamps. Ignore the
# root build tree outright, plus the dh-generated artifacts in case the
# build writes back through a symlink into packaging/debian/.
/debian/
/packaging/debian/linsync/
/packaging/debian/cargo_home/
/packaging/debian/tmp/
/packaging/debian/files
/packaging/debian/.debhelper/
/packaging/debian/debhelper-build-stamp
/packaging/debian/*.substvars
/packaging/debian/*.debhelper.log
